FBIS4-51428 "drchi103_b_94001" FBIS-CHI-94-103 Daily Report 27 May 1994 United States & Canada Foreign Ministry `Welcomes' U.S. Decision on MFN, Rights Foreign Ministry `Welcomes' U.S. Decision on MFN, Rights OW2705040894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0355 GMT 27 May 94 OW2705040894 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Beijing, May 27 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry said today that China welcomes U.S. President Bill Clinton's decision to renew China's most favored nation (MFN) trading status for 1994-95 and to delink the future MFN renewal from human rights issues. In a statement just released here, the ministry said that Clinton's decision would create a favorable condition for further strengthening and expanding trade and economic cooperation between the two countries, helping improve and develop bilateral relations, and therefore is in the fundamental interest of the two countries and the two peoples. Saying that the Chinese Government and Chinese people welcome Clinton's decision, the Chinese Foreign Ministry also urged an early lift of all the existing sanctions imposed on China by the United States.
